{
  "texts": [
    "In another study, Romero et al. (2020) introduce a novel approach combining optical superresolution microscopy with DL to improve the taxonomic resolution with which fossil pollen are identified.",
    "Three CNN based models, namely, models-Maximum Projection Model (MPM), Multislice Model (MSM), and Fused Model (FM), were developed to classify pollen from 16 genera of the legume tribe Amherstieae.",
    "The FM architecture, which integrates both external and internal morphological features by combining maximum intensity projections and selected slices from the image stack, showed the highest accuracy.",
    "The models utilize simple code composition for feature extraction and multiway softmax classification, with FM's combined approach allowing for a more comprehensive representation of morphological traits.",
    "Poor preservation can hinder the model's ability to consistently differentiate between genera, particularly when fossil specimens are incomplete or degraded."
  ]
}